Title: IMPROVED SOLA INVERSIONS OF MDI DATA  
Author: R.M. Larsen J. Christensen-Dalsgaard ; A.G. Kosovichev J. Schou W.W. Hansen 
Keyword: Key words: Helioseismic inversion; SOLA method; solar rotation  
Address: DK-8000 Arhus C, Denmark  DK-8000 Arhus C, Denmark 3 Teoretisk Astrofysik Center, Danmarks Grundforskningsfond, Denmark  Stanford, CA 94305-4085, U.S.A.  
Affiliation: 1 Datalogisk Institut, Aarhus Universitet,  Institut for Fysik og Astronomy, Aarhus Universitet,  Experimental Physics Laboratory, Stanford University,  
Abstract: We invert rotational splitting data (up to degree 250) from one year of SOI-MDI data, using the SOLA inversion method. We present an improved version of SOLA, where the target functions have been modified to match the behavior of the kernels for rotational splitting coefficients near the rotation axis. A test of the robustness of the improved method is carried out by inverting artificial data from the MDI Hare and Hounds exercise. This shows that these modifications improve the effective resolution near the pole, which allows us to assess more reliably the nature of the high-latitude features seen with other inversion methods. We analyze the averaging kernels and the error correlation between different points in the solution, the latter being a potential source of spurious features in the solutions. 
